Smugglers Cottage overlooking an ancient smugglers’ cove on Cornwall’s north coast is on the market for £3million . 
  Estate agents said they have seen an increase in interest in holiday homes since Poldark began airing last month . 
  Summer and winter cottages are linked via a lift and have stunning views of Smugglers Cove . 
  Boasting seven bedrooms and seven bathrooms the property has direct access to the beach . 
 